&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Account Development team partners with merchants across Canada to unlock their full growth potential on DoorDash. Our mission is to give every merchant the tools to grow first-party sales, deliver standout guest experiences, and operate more efficiently. Backed by a powerful suite of products — including Drive On-Demand, Online Ordering, and more — we equip merchants to scale their business on their terms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for driven sales professionals to join us as Associate Strategic Account Development Executives. This is a virtual-first, high-velocity sales role where you will introduce merchants to the DoorDash Commerce Platform, run product demos, and guide them through the full sales cycle—from initial outreach to signed agreement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this team, you’ll build deep product expertise, guide merchants through implementation requirements, and help them modernize their digital ordering experience. This team plays a critical role in scaling DoorDash’s next major product line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll report to a Strategic Account Development Manager and work primarily with the outbound Commerce Platform team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is fully remote with minimal travel, and the majority of selling is done via cold outreach, outbound prospecting, and Zoom-based discovery and demos.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run a complete, fast-paced sales cycle, from cold outreach through signed contract and handoff to Implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive high-volume pipeline management across a large book of SMB accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct virtual discovery, demos, and product recommendations tailored to merchant needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate merchants on key components of the DoorDash Commerce Platform, including POS integrations, ordering channels, loyalty features, and data insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address technical and operational objections (e.g., integration capabilities, resource constraints, competing priorities).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted advisor, helping merchants understand how Commerce Platform can grow revenue and improve operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams—including Account Managers, Marketing, and Implementation—to ensure a smooth onboarding experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence product adoption and play a key role in scaling DoorDash’s next major platform offering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 3+ years of closing experience in a high-velocity environment (less may qualify for President’s Club-level performers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a true hunter, with strong discovery skills and experience conducting outbound prospecting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You excel at explaining value propositions, handling objections, and guiding merchants through technical decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can manage a fast-paced pipeline and maintain exceptional organization across a high volume of active prospects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re comfortable selling SaaS solutions; restaurant tech experience is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You demonst

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Canadian DoorDash Customer Growth team focuses on building differentiated consumer experiences and supporting our Restaurants, New Verticals, and Ads &amp;amp; Promotions businesses. Our team&#39;s goals are to build an increasingly personalized in-app experience, create memorable consumer moments by leveraging relevant use cases, and unlock sustainable growth for DoorDash Canada. Our team provides an exciting opportunity to collaborate to create impact and be part of a global company that is evolving how local economies grow.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Strategy &amp;amp; Operations Associate role is for self-motivated, curious, and ownership-minded individuals who think through a customer-first lens, thrive on solving complex problems using data, collaborate across all levels of the organization, and execute their ideas efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will be a key contributor to the Consumer Experience team, primarily responsible for building the in-app merchandising experience for strategic bets across DoorDash Canada. The scope will include supporting key campaigns by creating the right experiences and strategies for customer growth, leveraging data to optimize existing and new initiatives. Success will be measured on the ability to support and hit OKRs as they relate to the above.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be part of the Customer Growth team and report to the Strategy &amp;amp; Operations Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build&lt;/strong&gt; - You are excited to work on something that hasn&#39;t been done before. Your job will include building experiences and launching plans from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategize&lt;/strong&gt; - Develop DoorDash&#39;s path to excellence using first principles &amp;amp; empathy, identify trends that emerge and know when to double down and when to try something new.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment &lt;/strong&gt;- Use data to run tests on everything from promotional campaigns to new in-app creative assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze &lt;/strong&gt;- Assess the operational and financial impacts of your decisions and iterate given insights. Continuously seek new improvements that can be made to the experience leveraging performance data.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate&lt;/strong&gt; - Work with a variety of teams including marketing, merchant, product, engineering, finance and analytics to execute on plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive both as a generalist and specialist who can build the overarching strategy and dive deep into specific issues &amp;amp; processes to drive continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a self-starter who is biased towards action and excels in a fast-paced environment and evolving business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable with ambiguity and bring structure, organization, and focus to your work and cross-functional teams, including product, marketing, finance, and legal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a problem solver and can identify the core problem and determine

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DoorDash&#39;s Consumer Lifecycle Marketing team in Canada is responsible for building lasting relationships with our customers through personalized, scalable, cross-channel experiences that drive engagement and long-term value. The Core Marketplace pod focuses on the heart of DoorDash&#39;s Canadian business — ensuring customers engage, retain, and return to the platform for food delivery and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a strategic, solution-oriented, and creative retention marketer to join the Canada Consumer Lifecycle Marketing team. In this role, you will focus on launching and iterating on CRM programs that drive growth and retention for our core marketplace business in Canada.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is able to think big picture about the customer lifecycle in one moment and seamlessly transition into the details of campaign execution and reporting in the next. They have experience building consensus with cross-functional teams, developing trusted relationships with partners, and excelling at making data-informed decisions to accomplish campaign and business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key areas of focus include: creating and maintaining campaign and workflow strategy for Canada Core MAU efforts, including offer, cadence, and audience testing; analyzing the impact of initiatives on key business metrics; creative ideation and iteration; and consulting on strategy for various customer workstreams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Canada Core Marketplace lifecycle strategy — develop and execute CRM programs that drive engagement, retention, and resurrection for DoorDash&#39;s core Canadian customer base&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build end-to-end campaigns &lt;/strong&gt;— manage audience segmentation, targeting, creative briefing, QA, launch, and post-campaign reporting within Braze&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and iterate on customer journeys — build trigger-based and always-on CRM programs that meet customers at key moments in their lifecycle (e.g. onboarding, re-engagement, win-back)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally — collaborate with Product, Analytics, Promo Strategy, Creative Studio, and Marketing Ops to deliver cohesive lifecycle programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze and optimize &lt;/strong&gt;— review campaign and program performance with analytics partners, identify trends, and translate findings into actionable improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on best practices — bring relevant learnings on lifecycle marketing, retention strategies, and CRM innovation to the broader team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re excited about you because you have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in CRM or lifecycle marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with CRM technology including ESPs and marketing automation platforms (e.g. Braze, Iterable, Salesforce Marketing Cloud)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical mindset with strong attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writer and communicator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of SQL, HTML, and data visualization platforms (e.g. Tableau, Periscope)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of email

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DoorDash’s mission is to grow and empower local economies. By building intelligent, last-mile delivery technology for local cities, DoorDash connects people with the local businesses they care about — helping grow businesses and the communities that support those businesses. To further this mission, we’re looking for an experienced marketer who will sit at the intersection of growth, brand and operations, to develop integrated marketing strategies that deliver for DashPass members everyday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate Manager on the DashPass Integrated Marketing team to own high-impact priorities that deepen DashPass member engagement across Canada, offering them a best-in-class subscription experience. In this role, you will use insights to develop consumer-first strategies to retain and engage DashPass members, and work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure we are serving members’ needs, maximizing DoorDash value from our partner relationships, and driving our business forward.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act as the lynchpin between marketing teams&lt;/strong&gt; (Lifecycle, Media, Creative Studio), Strategy &amp;amp; Operations, Product, Finance, and Analytics to build and execute on integrated marketing campaigns for DashPass Canada&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strengthen the membership experience&lt;/strong&gt; by partnering closely with the Lifecycle, Operations and Product teams to create compelling member experiences and value that make DashPass membership worth it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive key strategic partnerships&lt;/strong&gt; that fuel DashPass member growth and deliver meaningful value to members across Canada&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify and execute on opportunities&lt;/strong&gt; to increase DashPass subscriber retention in Canada, while establishing the role of marketing and how we can bring more value to our members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create process where process doesn’t exist&lt;/strong&gt; across key DashPass initiatives to streamline operations and foster a productive team culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive the quarterly marketing goals&lt;/strong&gt; and KPIs, and contribute to reporting to track their progress in partnership with Analytics, S&amp;amp;O and channel teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive cross-functional meetings&lt;/strong&gt; and own end-to-end project trackers to rally key stakeholders towards a shared goal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish reporting cadence&lt;/strong&gt; across performance and retention campaigns, while driving action plans to grow our paid subscriber balance and reduce churn quarter over quarter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify gaps in consumer insights and create testing plans&lt;/strong&gt; in partnership with Marketing Insights and Research teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create positioning and messaging frameworks&lt;/strong&gt; for our lifecycle audiences, and establish testing plans that optimize DashPass value props to drive the highest conversion rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Merchant is at the core of DoorDash. The Merchant Team, one of the largest in the company, powers many facets of our business and is one of the primary drivers of growth and revenue. On the Merchant Strategy &amp;amp; Ops team, our mission is to have best-in class restaurant selection, build cutting edge services for our merchants to grow their business, and help our partners operate seamlessly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an operator with a strong bias to action who loves using data and getting creative to solve problems. You’ll join our Merchant Selection team, where we operate relentlessly towards ensuring we strike the best possible deals with our merchants, to enable us to grow our restaurant selection in a sustainable manner. Specifically, you will take ownership of our Merchant Retention function. This role is critical in helping ensure DoorDash maintains the existing selection on our platform, by partnering closely with our account teams to drive value for both our merchants and DoorDash. You will size and model deal opportunities, develop new processes to predict and prevent churn, build compelling packages for our sales teams to pitch and will be responsible for making strategic tradeoffs to find the optimal investments for us to deploy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategize –&lt;/strong&gt; Devise and execute initiatives against the overall Selection strategy, focused on how we can get the most out of our agreements with merchants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimize –&lt;/strong&gt; Build the best merchant revenue engine so DoorDash continues to offer the highest quality selection for its customers and retain our merchants&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner: &lt;/strong&gt;You love equipping other teams with what they need to be successful. You are able to take feedback and put it into action.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because you have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in consulting, strategy, finance, analytics or business operations experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial modelling experience is required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of analytical problem solving, managing cross-functional initiatives and stake-holders, and succeeding in a fast moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An analytical mindset and can deliver actionable recommendations out of complex datasets; SQL experience is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors Degree or higher&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actual compensation within the pay range listed below will be decided based on factors including, but not limited to, skills, prior relevant experience, and specific work location. Base salary is localized according to employee work location.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to base salary, the compensation for this role includes opportunities for equity grants. Talk to your recruiter for more

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dasher &amp;amp; Logistics team ensures every delivery is completed with speed, accuracy, and a positive experience for consumers, merchants, and Dashers. We own the health of our delivery marketplace — including cost, quality, efficiency, fulfillment, and sustainable growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within this organization, the Canada team owns end-to-end marketplace performance for the country. We partner closely with Product, Engineering, Finance, Analytics, Marketing, and Operations to operate and improve one of DoorDash’s most dynamic and complex markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring an Associate Manager, Strategy &amp;amp; Operations to help manage Dasher supply and delivery quality across Canadian markets. This role sits at the intersection of operational execution and marketplace health, and is accountable for ensuring the right number of quality Dashers are available to meet demand reliably across geographies and conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will translate company and regional goals into clear supply strategies, balancing Dasher acquisition, mobilization, and retention to maintain a healthy and high-performing supply base. You will manage key supply levers, including onboarding pipelines, retention programs, and regional coverage optimization. Your work will require a sharp understanding of what drives Dasher behavior and engagement, and how to design programs that attract and retain quality Dashers at the right time and place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role means building and managing supply frameworks that consistently meet demand while maintaining strong delivery quality, even as market conditions, seasonality, and external factors shift. You will lead structured analyses to identify supply gaps, diagnose root causes, and drive durable improvements in coverage and quality across geographies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report into a Manager of Strategy &amp;amp; Operations. We expect this role to be hybrid with some time in-office and some time remote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Dasher supply health across Canadian markets, managing across acquisition, mobilization, and retention to ensure demand is reliably met with strong quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose and close supply gaps across regions, using data to identify root causes and deploy targeted interventions across different market conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and optimize programs that attract and retain quality Dashers, understanding what drives engagement and how to sustain a healthy supply base over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage supply across varying operating conditions including weather, local events, and seasonal demand shifts, balancing short-term actions with longer-term planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead rigorous, data-driven analyses to measure supply performance, model the impact of program changes, and surface clear recommendations for senior stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Product, Finance, Analytics, Legal, and Operations to align on supply strategy and deliver shared outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make thoughtful tradeoff decisions between supply adequacy, delivery quality, and cost to protect long-term marketplace health&lt;/li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 data-local-id=&quot;36bb2d925857&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;heading&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 3 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;mark&quot; data-prosemirror-mark-name=&quot;strong&quot;&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;642384b1c909&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;New Verticals is building the future of local commerce by bringing new ways to delight our customers to market - beyond restaurants, across both the US and Canada. Think businesses like Grocery, Convenience, Alcohol, Retail and more to come! We are looking for top talent to play a pivotal role in growing our International New Verticals business! We are looking for someone who is excited about joining a fast-paced environment and driving our next wave of growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-local-id=&quot;2b808840c698&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;heading&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;mark&quot; data-prosemirror-mark-name=&quot;strong&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;bb7c138796dc&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;We are hiring two Associates based in Canada to support our New Verticals Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team. In these roles, you may be responsible for identifying, leading, and prioritizing initiatives to improve our operating rhythms across New Verticals, impacting both the US and Canadian businesses. You will lead short term execution, strategize long term plans and implement product features that may:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ak-ul&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;bulletList&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;listItem&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
