&lt;p&gt;The Operations Recruiting Team partners closely with Operations leaders to design and execute hiring strategies that bring exceptional talent into DoorDash — efficiently, thoughtfully, and at scale. As DoorDash expands its Canadian presence, this role offers a unique opportunity to support hiring across Operations, Sales, and Marketing — giving you broad exposure across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every hire we make directly impacts DoorDash&#39;s ability to grow, serve our customers, and win in the Canadian market. We&#39;re building a dedicated recruiting presence in Canada, and you&#39;ll help shape how we attract and hire talent across our Canadian teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a strategic, execution-oriented Senior Recruiter to support hiring across our Canadian business — spanning Operations, Sales, and Marketing functions. You&#39;ll own full-cycle recruiting across multiple business lines, partnering with stakeholders at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be expected to act as a true talent advisor — building relationships with senior stakeholders, establishing recruiting best practices in a new market, and delivering results in an ambiguous, fast-paced environment. You&#39;ll join a small Canada pod and use data, market insights, and emerging tools — including AI — to continuously raise the bar on talent and process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a strategic talent partner to Operations, Sales, and Marketing leadership — influencing hiring strategy, improving operational efficiency, and raising the bar on talent quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use funnel metrics, market insights, and recruiting data to identify inefficiencies, improve hiring velocity, and drive strong talent outcomes at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Finance, Compensation, HR, and business leaders across Ops, Sales, and Marketing to navigate complex hiring challenges and inform talent decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI and emerging technologies to improve sourcing strategies, recruiter productivity, stakeholder decision-making, and overall recruiting effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a collaborative, high-performing recruiting culture by sharing best practices and helping scale team impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 5+ years of full-cycle recruiting experience, ideally supporting Operations, Sales, and/or G&amp;amp;A functions in high-growth environments — and you have experience in the Canadian talent market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You operate as a strategic business partner — using data, market insights, and strong judgment to influence hiring decisions and improve recruiting efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in fast-paced, high-growth environments and know how to balance urgency, operational rigor, and exceptional candidate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re highly collaborative and build strong cross-functional partnerships with senior stakeholders across Operations, Sales, and G&amp;amp;A&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You actively leverage AI and emerging technologies to improve recruiting workflows, productivity, and

